# Git Standards

## Commit Messages

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).

**Format:** `type(scope): description`

- Present tense, imperative mood, lowercase
- Keep subject under 72 characters
- Reference issue number in body or footer: `Closes #8`

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `docs`, `style`, `perf`, `test`, `ci`

```bash
feat(seo): add sitemap.xml generation
fix(services): correct accordion height on mobile
chore(deps): update payload to 3.76
refactor(i18n): extract locale config to shared module
perf(images): lazy-load below-the-fold images
```

## Branch Naming

**Format:** `type/issue-number-short-description`

**Types:** `feature`, `bugfix`, `hotfix`, `chore`, `refactor`

```bash
feature/8-add-sitemap-robots
bugfix/15-fix-accordion-animation
chore/20-update-dependencies
refactor/25-extract-locale-utils
```

## Workflow

1. Always branch from `dev`
2. One branch per issue
3. Verify `npm run build` passes before committing
4. PR targets `dev`, include `Closes #N` in PR body
